==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Juno
<hw>Ju"no</hw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧"n⟦osl⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Junos</plw> <pr>(j⟦umac⟧"n⟦osl⟧z)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Rom. Myth.)</fld> <def>The queen of the Olympian
gods, the sister and wife of Jupiter, and the goddess who presided over
marriage. She corresponds to the Greek Hera.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Sweeter than the lids of <qex>Juno's</qex> eyes.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>One of the early discovered
asteroids.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Bird of Juno</b></col>, <cd>the peacock.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Junoesque</ent>⟦br⟧
